            "answer_text": "Andrew Wiles\u2019s original proof of Fermat\u2019s Last Theorem announced in 1993 was found to have an error when it was being reviewed for publication. Wiles corrected the error and a revised proof was published in 1995. Calling it a \u201cmistake\u201d is not really fair. It was more that one part of it was incompletely proved. Wiles\u2019s proof ran to 150 pages and presented a wealth of new techniques and proofs for related conjectures; it wasn\u2019t as he he forgot to carry a 1. It wasn\u2019t really controversial, though Wiles found it professionally embarrassing. ",
