            "answer_text": "Most controversies in maths arise not because a mistake was missed, but because obvious truths, in retrospect anyway, haven't been recognised. Years, sometimes centuries later, mathematicians have to rebuild a lot of mathematics, and many of them are quite dogmatic. A famous example is the mathematical revolution of the early 20th century. There have to be examples of what you asked about as well, but I can't come up with any. ",
